commit.message:
Always calculate libdir

flatpak-builder relies on patched cmake and meson from
freedesktop-sdk to change libdir from lib64 to lib on 64bit
distributions. This dependency is *weird* since it's actually
flatpak that sets up the dynamic linker paths. Instead, put
responsibility for setting up correct libdir to flatpak-builder
always.
Update libglnx commit

Fix memory leaks

Found by building a package while built with libasan

Signed-off-by: Hubert Figuière <hub@figuiere.net>

workflows: Exercise `make distcheck` in CI

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

tests: Ensure all test files are in the dist tarball

Otherwise, the tests will fail when built from the dist tarball.

Also install it if "as-installed" tests are enabled, so that it can be
used in those tests too.

Resolves: https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak-builder/issues/585
Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

manifest: Don't emit empty id in `provides` when renaming

Followup from https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak-builder/pull/579

Signed-off-by: Hubert Figuière <hub@figuiere.net>

manifest: Add disable-http-decompression option

Some servers are broken so to avoid unusable sources this lets
you opt-out of decompression.

manifest: Properly change the app id in the appstream file

Also update the `provides` if necessary.

Issue https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak-builder/issues/90

tests: Test appdata rename

Clarify warning when rename-icon includes a file extension

Add support for 'autoprune-unless' for extensions

This is an existing flatpak feature that was never added to
flatpak-builder, so it couldn't be used in app manifests.
Fix uninitialized warnings
Remove unused code
Fix deprecation warnings from glib 2.70 API

Add a note that app-id is deprecated

This was soft deprecated in https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak-builder/commit/3341fb08adc981879043445e8c40883786705738#diff-fe51491bafa983ec48ccdaa2da758238ee9d5623e20cea285cae410d22dd645dR359-R365
in favour of "id" which aligns with appstream

https://github.com/ximion/appstream/commit/8b412031037ea08028279e9408ea0eda01938c48

Issue #1 - Rename mime files and icons

- Added rename-mime-file and rename-mime-icons.

https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak-builder/issues/1
Enable compressed downloads

tests: Add a test for rename

- install test icon in the proper directory
- added desktop file

tests: Actually test the output of both .yaml and .json

- also install and test icons with the correct app-id.

Reimplement support for data URIs

With the move from libsoup libcurl doesn't handle data URIs.

So this imports the code from libsoup which isn't overly complex.

Set a download speed timeout in the curl session

This will abort the download if it’s slower than 10KB/sec for 60 seconds
with CURLE_OPERATION_TIMEDOUT

The limits are copied from https://github.com/flatpak/flatpak/commit/d6b10c26efd583805ec7085c040a52d0884c305b

This seems it could be useful in CI which may want to proactively kill a
pipeline if a download timeouts
